1
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:22,125
[distant footsteps]

2
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:24,208
[SHISUI]
Everything okay?

3
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:26,166
Of course.

4
00:00:26,250 --> 00:00:27,625
[thud]

5
00:00:28,916 --> 00:00:30,208
[SHISUI]
Did you kill her?

6
00:00:30,291 --> 00:00:34,166
[KAMUI] An Enforcer did.
Does it hurt to hear that?

7
00:00:34,250 --> 00:00:35,708
[SHISUI]
I don't know.

8
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:40,333
[SHISUI] I guess
I feel a little sad.

9
00:00:40,416 --> 00:00:43,291
[KAMUI] You've been following
my dosage instructions.

10
00:00:43,375 --> 00:00:46,208
So let's see
how your Hue's doing.

11
00:00:46,291 --> 00:00:47,750
Hm.

12
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:49,250
All clear.

13
00:00:51,083 --> 00:00:53,458
[SHISUI] To think that just by
taking a bit of that medicine

14
00:00:53,541 --> 00:00:56,791
I'm better. And after
they said it wouldn't work.

15
00:00:56,875 --> 00:00:59,166
Medicine should be
tailored to the person.

16
00:00:59,250 --> 00:01:02,416
Taking a one-size-fits-all
approach with strong doses

17
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:05,208
is just another
form of violence.

18
00:01:06,541 --> 00:01:09,875
Why's it so important
to you that I become clear?

19
00:01:09,958 --> 00:01:12,708
[KAMUI] Because I want
you to have your own will.

20
00:01:13,791 --> 00:01:15,208
[SHISUI] My own will?

21
00:01:15,291 --> 00:01:16,708
[KAMUI] Yeah.

22
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:20,625
[KAMUI] Stay by my side.

23
00:01:24,750 --> 00:01:28,208
[SHISUI] Okay. I'll do anything.

24
00:01:29,083 --> 00:01:31,541
That's good to know.

25
00:01:32,541 --> 00:01:36,041
[KAMUI] Sibyl.
It won't be long now...

26
00:01:36,125 --> 00:01:38,916
before I bring you to justice.

27
00:01:42,750 --> 00:01:46,333
All right then. I'm going
to go check the back door.

28
00:01:46,416 --> 00:01:48,708
Okay.

29
00:01:48,791 --> 00:01:52,416
[MIKA retches]

30
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:04,666
[MIKA retches]

31
00:02:07,916 --> 00:02:09,708
[DOMINATOR] Crime
Coefficient, twenty-six.

32
00:02:09,791 --> 00:02:11,958
Target is a
registered Inspector.

33
00:02:12,041 --> 00:02:13,250
[beeping]

34
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:15,125
[DOMINATOR] Warning.
Any rebellious conduct by

35
00:02:15,208 --> 00:02:18,875
an Enforcer will be recorded
and reported to headquarters.

36
00:02:20,208 --> 00:02:22,416
[SAKUYA] She stays so clear.

37
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:32,333
What the hell was that?

38
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:06,166
[AKANE] Impressive
as usual, Professor.

39
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:08,583
You've finished reading all
of the case files already?

40
00:04:08,666 --> 00:04:10,083
[SAIGA] I have but
if anyone should be

41
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:11,875
impressed here, it's me.

42
00:04:13,375 --> 00:04:15,083
[SAIGA] It's only been a
day since the incident with

43
00:04:15,166 --> 00:04:17,250
the hostages at
the rehab facility.

44
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:20,833
And yet, you still come
across so calm and collected.

45
00:04:22,125 --> 00:04:25,125
[SAIGA] It's like
you're not even human.

46
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:27,375
[AKANE] That's a compliment?

47
00:04:28,791 --> 00:04:30,291
I'd be lying if I
told you their deaths

48
00:04:30,375 --> 00:04:32,500
weren't shocking, but still.

49
00:04:32,583 --> 00:04:34,166
I see all that
horror and it makes me

50
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:36,375
wanna work that much harder.

51
00:04:36,458 --> 00:04:37,833
Interesting.

52
00:04:37,916 --> 00:04:40,125
[AKANE]
Look, I'll get to the point.

53
00:04:40,208 --> 00:04:42,958
I want you to interrogate
Representative Masuda.

54
00:04:43,041 --> 00:04:45,625
He's the politician,
is that right?

55
00:04:47,125 --> 00:04:48,375
[SAIGA] Is he calm now?

56
00:04:48,458 --> 00:04:51,875
[AKANE] Yes. Unnaturally so.

57
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,625
And that calm demeanor
could be a set up

58
00:04:53,708 --> 00:04:55,333
for some kind of trap.

59
00:04:55,416 --> 00:04:58,541
That's what you're thinking
this means, isn't it?

60
00:04:58,625 --> 00:05:00,916
By analyzing call logs,
we've identified with

61
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:04,500
high confidence a potential
hiding location for Kamui.

62
00:05:04,583 --> 00:05:07,166
[AKANE] We've already
ordered in the Drones, but--

63
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:09,458
[police sirens]

64
00:05:09,541 --> 00:05:11,250
You'll probably still
want to lead a team

65
00:05:11,333 --> 00:05:13,875
there yourself to be certain.

66
00:05:13,958 --> 00:05:15,416
[AKANE] The call
Inspector Aoyanagi

67
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,875
got from Inspector Shisui.

68
00:05:17,958 --> 00:05:19,833
We're a hundred
percent certain the voice

69
00:05:19,916 --> 00:05:21,666
on the phone belonged to her.

70
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:24,666
But if Kamui's someone who
can win over an Inspector,

71
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:28,250
there's no way he would ever
let us get the drop on him.

72
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:33,916
Let's say he's that
good. What's your plan?

73
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,583
[AKANE] I think we have
to be on guard at all times.

74
00:05:36,666 --> 00:05:39,708
His Psycho-Pass, it's
undetectable despite the fact

75
00:05:39,791 --> 00:05:42,291
he must've been
at the crime scene.

76
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:45,375
[SAIGA] Does any of
this remind you of...

77
00:05:45,458 --> 00:05:47,458
Shogo Makishima?

78
00:05:48,541 --> 00:05:51,666
[AKANE] I'd say the overall
creepiness factor is similar,

79
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:53,291
but beyond that, no.

80
00:05:53,375 --> 00:05:55,541
Something is definitely
different this time.

81
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:58,333
[SAIGA] If we can figure
out what that "something" is,

82
00:05:58,416 --> 00:06:01,750
we'll be close to understanding
Kamui's true character.

83
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:03,125
And that's one
of the main reasons

84
00:06:03,208 --> 00:06:05,708
why I came to you,
Professor Saiga.

85
00:06:05,791 --> 00:06:07,458
Sorry to disappoint, Inspector,

86
00:06:07,541 --> 00:06:08,750
but I'm not a magician.

87
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:11,083
I can't simply wave a
wand and pull a rabbit,

88
00:06:11,166 --> 00:06:13,375
[SAIGA] let alone
the truth, out of a hat.

89
00:06:13,458 --> 00:06:16,041
Oh, don't be so modest.

90
00:06:18,958 --> 00:06:20,083
[SAIGA] Are you heading out?

91
00:06:20,166 --> 00:06:21,083
[AKANE] Yes.

92
00:06:21,166 --> 00:06:23,333
[SAIGA] Be very careful, Akane.

93
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:25,791
[AKANE] Division Three is
joining the investigation.

94
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:29,041
They should provide a
nice boost in firepower.

95
00:06:29,125 --> 00:06:32,166
[SAIGA] I'm surprised Chief
Kasei has given her "okay."

96
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:35,916
Or perhaps she isn't really
keen on this particular gambit,

97
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:40,750
but is simply going along with
it as a way to hedge her bets.

98
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:43,875
As usual, very impressive.

99
00:06:43,958 --> 00:06:45,958
[KASEI] I am well aware
that her actions in this

100
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:49,125
investigation have
no validity whatsoever.

101
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:51,625
But it's easier for us to
manage her if we keep her

102
00:06:51,708 --> 00:06:53,833
in the chain of command,
rather than letting her

103
00:06:53,916 --> 00:06:57,208
off the leash and allowing
her to act on her own.

104
00:06:58,166 --> 00:06:59,333
[KASEI] In any event,

105
00:06:59,416 --> 00:07:01,458
our losses so far aren't
severe enough to warrant

106
00:07:01,541 --> 00:07:04,708
taking any action. Though
I suppose it will require

107
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:06,875
some time to find
suitable replacements

108
00:07:06,958 --> 00:07:08,916
for the Inspectors
that we've lost.

109
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,958
[KASEI] As for the Enforcers
they've left behind,

110
00:07:12,041 --> 00:07:14,041
we can simply place
them with other Inspectors

111
00:07:14,125 --> 00:07:16,083
to keep them working.

112
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:20,333
Kaede Hasuike. Just
reassigned to Division One.

113
00:07:20,416 --> 00:07:22,250
Look forward to
working with you.

114
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:23,708
Uh--!

115
00:07:29,791 --> 00:07:31,750
Thanks for the warm welcome.

116
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:36,916
♪

117
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,833
[doors open]

118
00:07:39,916 --> 00:07:41,583
[doors close]

119
00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:45,125
[GINOZA] I heard the news.

120
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:47,458
You've been transferred
to Division One.

121
00:07:47,541 --> 00:07:51,375
[MALE ENFORCER] Yes.
You and Inspector Aoyanagi--

122
00:07:51,458 --> 00:07:53,250
started here
the same year, right?

123
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:55,041
You were friends?

124
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:57,750
[GINOZA] She was also
your boss, wasn't she?

125
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:59,541
I didn't mean to--

126
00:07:59,625 --> 00:08:01,125
[GINOZA] You performed
enforcement on a

127
00:08:01,208 --> 00:08:05,125
latent criminal. You did your
job. Nothing wrong with that.

128
00:08:05,208 --> 00:08:06,833
[MALE ENFORCER] But if I had--

129
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:09,083
[GINOZA] Just--
try to stay out of my sight

130
00:08:09,166 --> 00:08:11,416
for a little while, okay?

131
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,291
[huffs]

132
00:08:15,458 --> 00:08:17,666
[MIKA] I can't
help feeling scared.

133
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:22,416
Such terrible things
happened right before my eyes.

134
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:24,625
I tried to tell myself
it won't affect me,

135
00:08:24,708 --> 00:08:26,458
won't change me, but--

136
00:08:28,666 --> 00:08:30,208
Ms. Kunizuka--

137
00:08:30,291 --> 00:08:31,500
[gasps]

138
00:08:31,583 --> 00:08:36,166
♪

139
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:37,833
[KUNIZUKA] It's okay.

140
00:08:37,916 --> 00:08:41,333
Even Inspectors
need to cry sometimes.

141
00:08:41,416 --> 00:08:42,833
[MIKA] Thanks.

142
00:08:44,958 --> 00:08:46,583
[MIKA] Yayoi?

143
00:08:46,666 --> 00:08:48,750
Yeah?

144
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,416
[MIKA] I was
just wondering...

145
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:54,583
Sakuya Togane.
What's your read on him?

146
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:56,666
I think that he's an
excellent Enforcer with

147
00:08:56,750 --> 00:09:00,166
outstanding judgment who
performs his job impeccably.

148
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:02,791
[MIKA] Oh, good.

149
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:08,416
[KASEI] I see.
So I'm in charge of this

150
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:11,250
particular case now, am I?

151
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,708
[KASEI] Very well, but no
matter how much you want to

152
00:09:14,791 --> 00:09:18,583
blame me for it, I can't
accept responsibility...

153
00:09:18,666 --> 00:09:20,541
because there's simply
nothing that I can do

154
00:09:20,625 --> 00:09:22,375
that will alter the past.

155
00:09:23,583 --> 00:09:25,791
Let's just try to
make the best of the situation

156
00:09:25,875 --> 00:09:27,833
that's been presented to us.

157
00:09:27,916 --> 00:09:30,833
[KASEI] Perhaps it might
even help us to evolve.

158
00:09:30,916 --> 00:09:34,125
Besides, aren't you curious...

159
00:09:34,208 --> 00:09:35,958
...to see how
she'll be affected

160
00:09:36,041 --> 00:09:38,541
when confronted by "that"?

161
00:09:39,666 --> 00:09:41,666
[AKANE] We'll be arriving soon.

162
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:45,416
It's a site where
they test Military Drones.

163
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,791
[AKANE] Our mission is
strictly to investigate.

164
00:09:47,875 --> 00:09:49,708
However, as a
precautionary measure,

165
00:09:49,791 --> 00:09:52,291
risk level B weapons
will be permitted.

166
00:09:52,375 --> 00:09:54,833
In addition, this is a
joint operation between

167
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:56,958
Division One and Division Three.

168
00:09:57,041 --> 00:09:59,333
I expect all Enforcers
to be mindful of

169
00:09:59,416 --> 00:10:02,416
the situation and obey
any order given to you,

170
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:04,000
regardless of
whether it comes from

171
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:06,875
your own lead
Inspector or another one.

172
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:09,791
Thought I'd go my
whole life without

173
00:10:09,875 --> 00:10:11,541
ever coming back here.

174
00:10:11,625 --> 00:10:13,541
[MIKA] Inspector, is there
a reason you need to take

175
00:10:13,625 --> 00:10:15,291
so many people with you?

176
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:18,833
[AKANE] The personnel allotment
was dictated by the Chief.

177
00:10:18,916 --> 00:10:21,375
Between the
interrogation of Masuda,

178
00:10:21,458 --> 00:10:23,541
[MIKA] and the analysis of
the barricade incident site,

179
00:10:23,625 --> 00:10:25,375
not to mention the
Holo examination

180
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:27,166
you personally requested,

181
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:28,875
we've got our
plate so full here

182
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:30,583
it's about to topple over!

183
00:10:30,666 --> 00:10:32,416
[AKANE] I assigned everyone
only what I thought

184
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:35,416
they could handle. Did I
overestimate your abilities?

185
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:36,916
[MIKA] I'm just saying
there's a whole lot of stuff

186
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,458
for us to deal with.

187
00:10:38,541 --> 00:10:40,416
Besides, the Drones have
already gone over every inch

188
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:42,583
of that place looking for
evidence, haven't they?

189
00:10:42,666 --> 00:10:44,125
[AKANE] Some things
you can only learn by

190
00:10:44,208 --> 00:10:45,958
seeing them with your own eyes.

191
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:48,250
Seriously? That way of
thinking is so archaic.

192
00:10:48,333 --> 00:10:49,916
[AKANE] You know, the
newest methods and ideas

193
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,875
aren't always the best.

194
00:10:51,958 --> 00:10:53,500
We're here now. I've gotta go.

195
00:10:56,458 --> 00:10:57,375
Mmh.

196
00:10:57,458 --> 00:10:59,083
[KUNIZUKA]
Inspector Shimotsuki.

197
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:02,041
It's the Ministry of Welfare.
They're all in a tizzy,

198
00:11:02,125 --> 00:11:04,041
demanding that we release
Representative Masuda

199
00:11:04,125 --> 00:11:05,500
now that his Hue is improving.

200
00:11:05,583 --> 00:11:07,541
Here, take a look for yourself.

201
00:11:09,583 --> 00:11:11,000
[KUNIZUKA] No matter
how you look at it,

202
00:11:11,083 --> 00:11:13,416
someone's putting
pressure on us.

203
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:16,250
The enduring greatness of
Japanese society has always

204
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:19,458
been held aloft by the strength
and vitality of its...

205
00:11:19,541 --> 00:11:21,750
Much as we might like,
we can't refuse a request

206
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:23,625
from the Ministry of Welfare.

207
00:11:23,708 --> 00:11:25,416
[SHION] Even if we play
dumb, we can probably only

208
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:28,708
buy ourselves a day
or two at the most.

209
00:11:28,791 --> 00:11:30,625
[MASUDA] more than
any other, is provi--

210
00:11:31,333 --> 00:11:33,625
[MALE ENFORCER] This area used
to be a major trading port.

211
00:11:33,708 --> 00:11:37,083
After that closed, it became
an unmanned storage yard.

212
00:11:38,791 --> 00:11:40,666
[MALE ENFORCER] Then, the
Ministry of National Defense's

213
00:11:40,750 --> 00:11:43,791
Military Drones R&amp;D
Division set up shop.

214
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:50,625
[MAN] We have more than
enough room for the Drones,

215
00:11:50,708 --> 00:11:53,333
as well as parts and
supplies for their servicing.

216
00:11:53,416 --> 00:11:56,958
And being mostly unmanned,
makes accidents very unlikely.

217
00:11:57,041 --> 00:11:58,833
[MAN] There's no safer
place for troubleshooting

218
00:11:58,916 --> 00:12:01,416
and activating Military Drones.

219
00:12:03,375 --> 00:12:05,583
Interesting.

220
00:12:10,291 --> 00:12:11,666
Whoa!

221
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:25,625
Let's see if we
can sync information

222
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:27,000
with more than two Drones.

223
00:12:27,083 --> 00:12:29,708
[MALE OPERATOR] Hey!
Sugo, is that you?

224
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:31,166
[sighs]

225
00:12:32,875 --> 00:12:35,541
[MALE OPERATOR]
Wow. It's been a while!

226
00:12:35,625 --> 00:12:38,166
Man I haven't seen you
since you left for rehab.

227
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:40,291
So when did you
get back on the job?

228
00:12:40,375 --> 00:12:43,083
[sighs] I don't
work here anymore.

229
00:12:43,166 --> 00:12:44,291
[MALE OPERATOR] What?

230
00:12:44,375 --> 00:12:46,666
I'm an Enforcer
with the Bureau.

231
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:50,458
Uh. Oh. I had no idea.

232
00:12:50,541 --> 00:12:53,833
[SUGO] I gotta go.
I'm still on the clock.

233
00:12:56,791 --> 00:12:59,791
He worked here,
in his prior life.

234
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:02,083
[DIVISION 3 INSPECTOR]
Things look normal.

235
00:13:02,166 --> 00:13:06,250
[SUZUKI sighs] I say we just
sit tight until we get orders.

236
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:08,708
Division One. That's who
should be taking the lead,

237
00:13:08,791 --> 00:13:11,750
since this whole
investigation is their baby.

238
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:14,666
They do seem to be
the Chief's favorites.

239
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:15,750
[DIVISION 3 INSPECTOR]
Working with her is such a

240
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,500
pain in the ass.

241
00:13:18,958 --> 00:13:20,291
[SAKUYA] According
to the crew chief,

242
00:13:20,375 --> 00:13:23,333
this is a restricted area.
Authorized personnel only.

243
00:13:23,416 --> 00:13:26,791
He's sure it's deserted, but
you still have your doubts?

244
00:13:26,875 --> 00:13:29,250
It's true--scans haven't
detected anyone here

245
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:31,375
besides the staff.

246
00:13:31,458 --> 00:13:35,083
[AKANE] However, cymatic scans
are meaningless to a ghost.

247
00:13:37,166 --> 00:13:41,125
True. What he'd need to be
careful about are human eyes.

248
00:13:41,208 --> 00:13:44,041
[AKANE] He'd want a place
where scanners are installed,

249
00:13:44,125 --> 00:13:46,458
that's also deserted.

250
00:13:48,125 --> 00:13:49,750
[AKANE] Dead end.

251
00:13:53,375 --> 00:13:55,208
Mr. Togane?

252
00:13:55,291 --> 00:13:57,041
[SAKUYA]
The building on the left.

253
00:13:57,125 --> 00:14:00,458
Its emergency exits are placed
here on this street face.

254
00:14:00,541 --> 00:14:03,625
So then, wouldn't it also
make sense for the building

255
00:14:03,708 --> 00:14:05,375
[SAKUYA] next to it to
have something other than

256
00:14:05,458 --> 00:14:10,041
a blank wall? A structurally
unnecessary wall.

257
00:14:10,125 --> 00:14:12,666
Comfortably within the
range of cymatic scanners.

258
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:17,541
And located at the furthest end
of a typically deserted path.

259
00:14:18,708 --> 00:14:20,833
Holo.

260
00:14:20,916 --> 00:14:23,125
That's "detective's intuition."

261
00:14:27,166 --> 00:14:30,416
[MIKA] On the subject of
Inspector Tsunemori's conduct.

262
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:31,708
I have submitted a number of

263
00:14:31,791 --> 00:14:34,333
well-documented
reports to you, Chief.

264
00:14:34,416 --> 00:14:37,625
If possible, I would love
to hear your thoughts on them.

265
00:14:37,708 --> 00:14:39,833
Oh, yes.
Akane's conduct is of

266
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:42,000
no concern to me at the moment.

267
00:14:43,208 --> 00:14:44,708
[MIKA] With all due respect,
don't you think that's

268
00:14:44,791 --> 00:14:47,625
a dangerous position to take?

269
00:14:47,708 --> 00:14:48,750
Oh?

270
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:51,000
Her rough, hands-on approach.

271
00:14:51,083 --> 00:14:55,208
An obsession with flimsy clues
that's distorting her thinking.

272
00:14:55,291 --> 00:14:57,625
And her use of Enforcers.

273
00:14:57,708 --> 00:14:59,958
Those are just some
of the areas in which

274
00:15:00,041 --> 00:15:03,125
Inspector Tsunemori
has major deficiencies.

275
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,041
[KASEI] And your point is?

276
00:15:06,125 --> 00:15:08,250
[MIKA] I believe that helping
a colleague perform better

277
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:10,625
is in all of our best interests.

278
00:15:11,958 --> 00:15:14,166
Is that all you
wanted to discuss?

279
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:16,541
No. There's one more thing.

280
00:15:16,625 --> 00:15:18,000
[MIKA] I observed
a troubling action

281
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:20,625
by Enforcer Sakuya Togane.

282
00:15:21,916 --> 00:15:24,625
I see. I assume you
are referring to his

283
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:27,541
pointing a Dominator
at Inspector Akane.

284
00:15:27,625 --> 00:15:29,458
[MIKA] Yes.

285
00:15:29,541 --> 00:15:32,208
[KASEI] Just like you did, he
may have simply wanted to know

286
00:15:32,291 --> 00:15:35,166
if the Inspector's
mental state was healthy.

287
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:38,291
Though I concede it's not
the most responsible way.

288
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:40,125
Enforcers are latent criminals.

289
00:15:40,208 --> 00:15:43,750
Inspector Tsunemori doesn't
adequately consider their risk.

290
00:15:43,833 --> 00:15:47,208
I have no doubt this will
one day become a major issue.

291
00:15:47,291 --> 00:15:50,458
And when this does finally
happen could you please....

292
00:15:50,541 --> 00:15:53,750
give serious thought to
her course of treatment.

293
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:56,000
[KASEI] I'll think about it.

294
00:15:56,083 --> 00:15:59,000
That's all I ask.
Thank you, Chief Kasei.

295
00:15:59,916 --> 00:16:01,291
[doors open]

296
00:16:01,375 --> 00:16:02,875
[MIKA] Good day, ma'am.

297
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:04,958
[KASEI] Mmm.

298
00:16:05,041 --> 00:16:06,916
She'll be eaten alive.

299
00:16:09,208 --> 00:16:16,875
♪

300
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:18,791
[AKANE] This is...

301
00:16:23,166 --> 00:16:26,458
[SAKUYA]
A face transplant mask.

302
00:16:26,541 --> 00:16:30,333
Strange. What did
he need these for?

303
00:16:31,791 --> 00:16:34,541
In order for us to
maintain Japan's vitality,

304
00:16:34,625 --> 00:16:38,708
we must ensure the security and
well-being of all of her people.

305
00:16:38,791 --> 00:16:40,666
[MASUDA] This is a principle
I have fought for ever...

306
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:41,708
[SAIGA] What a farce.

307
00:16:41,791 --> 00:16:43,166
[SHION] Huh?

308
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:45,000
[MASUDA] ...it is one that
I will continue to fight for

309
00:16:45,083 --> 00:16:46,625
as long as I
have the privilege of

310
00:16:46,708 --> 00:16:48,916
serving the people
of this great nation.

311
00:16:50,125 --> 00:16:52,541
I've just been watching
videos of your speeches.

312
00:16:52,625 --> 00:16:55,541
Every one of them from
the past three years.

313
00:16:55,625 --> 00:16:58,041
You are quite the gifted orator.

314
00:16:58,125 --> 00:17:00,375
Though I suppose that is
a prerequisite of the job,

315
00:17:00,458 --> 00:17:02,666
isn't it? You can't be
a successful politician

316
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:04,666
[SAIGA] without
being a good speaker.

317
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:08,000
[SAIGA] One distinct quality
that I noticed you've

318
00:17:08,083 --> 00:17:10,541
demonstrated ever since
becoming a representative

319
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:12,791
is your mastery
of intonation.

320
00:17:12,875 --> 00:17:14,750
You purposely tone
it down when making

321
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:16,666
an important point,
and in doing so,

322
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:18,916
you demand the
audience's attention.

323
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,750
That balance is
a thing of beauty.

324
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:24,416
Or should I say, it was.

325
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:28,291
You had it down pat in all
of your earlier speeches.

326
00:17:28,375 --> 00:17:31,500
In comparison, your recent
efforts were lackluster.

327
00:17:31,583 --> 00:17:34,166
[SAIGA] Though you do
try hard to imitate him.

328
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:35,625
I wonder...

329
00:17:39,083 --> 00:17:40,875
[SAIGA] Who are you?

330
00:17:41,541 --> 00:17:42,791
[da-ding]

331
00:17:42,875 --> 00:17:43,875
[SUZUKI] Huh?

332
00:17:43,958 --> 00:17:45,166
[DIVISION 3 INSPECTOR]
Something wrong?

333
00:17:45,250 --> 00:17:47,125
The new Hungry
Chicken just came out!

334
00:17:47,208 --> 00:17:49,208
I don't think they
even announced it yet.

335
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:51,916
Wow, seriously,
how cool is that?

336
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,666
A video game? I told
you to put that crap away

337
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:56,208
[DIVISION 3 INSPECTOR]
when we're on duty.

338
00:17:56,291 --> 00:17:58,750
[SUZUKI] Oh, come on. Just let
me play a little. One level.

339
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,458
[chuckles]

340
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,125
Whoa.

341
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,000
[music and beeping from game]

342
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,375
[ding]

343
00:18:18,541 --> 00:18:19,916
[MALE OPERATOR] What the hell?

344
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:24,500
♪

345
00:18:25,416 --> 00:18:28,125
[music from game]

346
00:18:28,208 --> 00:18:31,041
♪

347
00:18:31,125 --> 00:18:33,041
Ha. Take that.

348
00:18:38,125 --> 00:18:40,125
[MALE OPERATOR C and D groan]

349
00:18:40,208 --> 00:18:41,666
Ah... eh!

350
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:43,833
[music from game]

351
00:18:43,916 --> 00:18:45,625
You can't hide!

352
00:18:50,916 --> 00:18:52,250
[SAKUYA] Inspector!

353
00:18:53,875 --> 00:18:56,125
Check it out.
Looks to me like somebody

354
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:58,833
must've been expecting us.

355
00:18:58,916 --> 00:19:00,291
[AKANE gasps]

356
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:05,208
I think that
you're a messenger.

357
00:19:05,291 --> 00:19:07,041
That you wanted to get caught.

358
00:19:07,125 --> 00:19:10,375
[SAIGA]
So you baited the MWPSB.

359
00:19:10,458 --> 00:19:12,458
But why are you doing this?

360
00:19:12,541 --> 00:19:15,125
What did you hope to achieve
by being brought in here,

361
00:19:15,208 --> 00:19:17,208
[SAIGA] talking about Kamui?

362
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:18,791
[MALE OPERATOR grunts]

363
00:19:18,875 --> 00:19:21,375
[panting]

364
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:24,125
It won't stop! But why?

365
00:19:29,041 --> 00:19:30,500
[yells]

366
00:19:35,166 --> 00:19:36,708
[AKANE and SAKUYA gasp]

367
00:19:36,791 --> 00:19:42,666
♪

368
00:19:42,750 --> 00:19:44,416
What the hell?

369
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:46,875
[music from game]

370
00:19:46,958 --> 00:19:48,166
[laughing]
[music from game]

371
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:50,791
[music from game]

372
00:19:51,541 --> 00:19:56,583
♪

373
00:19:56,666 --> 00:19:59,250
[MAN] What're you
